1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:04,223
All consumers with the same group.id form a consumer group.

2
00:00:04,173 --> 00:00:08,759
Kafka's Group Coordinator (a designated broker) manages group membership.

3
00:00:08,759 --> 00:00:21,096
When a group starts, the coordinator facilitates the JoinGroup / SyncGroup handshake: one consumer is elected the Group Leader, computes the partition assignment using a configured Assignor, and sends the assignment back through the coordinator.

4
00:00:21,096 --> 00:00:26,875
Real talk: Flipkart's Big Billion Day crashed their servers THREE times before they got this right.

